extends ../layout

block content

  .step#title
    h1 How to tell stories with data
    h3.bottom0 Digital Journalism Bootcamp
    p Tunis 2012 - Pierre Romera - <a href="http://twitter.com/pirhoo">@pirhoo</a>


  .step(data-x=990)
    h2 Get started with a definition*
    blockquote All activities related to the preparation of a newspaper or any other newspaper or magazine or audiovisual (<strong>collecting, selecting, formatting information </strong>) [...]
    ol.footnotes
      li Larousse dictionary <a href="http://www.larousse.fr/dictionnaires/francais/journalisme">http://www.larousse.fr/dictionnaires/francais/journalisme</a> [FR]

  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  //- COLLECTING
  //----------------------------------------------------------------------------
  .step(data-x=990*2)
    h2 Collecting
    p 
      | It's one of my favorite point, as a developer.<br />
      strong For a long time, journalists have to gather information.
    h3 But why is it so suitable?

  .step(data-x=990*2, data-y=400*1, data-rotate-x=-20)
    h3 Take a look to the last decade
    p.bottom10 Never before the information's sources have been so many.
    p.bottom10 Never before the information have circulated so easily.
    p Vox pops have become tweets. Messages circulate at 5 Mbps.
    h3.bottom10 Coming after the digital natives,<br />we are now in a world of data natives.
    p Swiming at any time in a global data ocean.
  
  .step(data-x=990*2, data-y=400*2, data-rotate-x=-20*2)
    h2.bottom10 <small>Everyday,</small> Facebook's users<small><br />produce the equivalent of <br /></small>120,000 DVD discs <small>of data</small>*
    p Just 2 days to cover a soccer field.
    ol.footnotes
      li Le Monde Informatique, August 2012 <a href="http://www.lemondeinformatique.fr/actualites/lire-facebook-supporte-500-to-de-nouvelles-donnees-par-jour-50140.html">http://bit.ly/P3mQns</a> [FR]

  .step(data-x=990*2,data-y=400*3, data-rotate-x=-20*3)
    h2.tc The <big>nature</big> of the information<br />had changed.      

  .step(data-x=990*2, data-rotate-y=180, data-y=400*3,  data-rotate-x=-20*3)
    h2.tc The <big>ways</big> to collect&nbsp;information had changed too.


